fKwMgWIYDwmwTp2KLp5j5xjVhdnthAInBK_4UkA60sooK_oMp3QmbMRnwfPpWT9GT0uUiV8nLuB=w224-h298-k-no-pi-0-ya186.83333-ro0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://sounddentistry.com/appointments/","source":"sounddentistry.com"},{"link":"https://search.opencare.com/results/24630130001?utm_source=google\u0026utm_medium=seo-direct-booking\u0026utm_content=main\u0026rwg_token=AFd1xnEpQ5zBJesIH49-rvgeyy8gAgGb8r4W0z_gLIQQCdWxfkV6THrMKxLJWPaECke0YOvj_ythzuAveMaVIBvxlA0PJkIJ8A%3D%3D","source":"opencare.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"118445140298457309891","name":"Sound Dentistry (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118445140298457309891"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"600 University St #818","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Transgender safespace","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Alex Filler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIq6Kt6soVgwDnRMuuzLZorWU-TxRsp_VTIWI0vI1qSt9ei1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best cleaning I've had since moving to Seattle! Crystal was both thorough and gentle, a hard combination to find in a dental setting. I left the office with a better understanding of my overall dental health, new floss, and a goodie bag.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Colin Sorensen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXpSKVQu1woH-en7nWOe0AwGoJY3QSUOgz60J56WqgGQZR5Q1lX2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This morning I showed up a hot mess, not knowing what my insurance provider was and being generally useless. Despite this throwing off their schedule (my apologies), the team was patient, kind, and oh-so-welcoming. I appreciated this very warm intro and am delighted to go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Madeline Feigles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJT6v43J4hTQ4rqPRj9koKqhHit4pCl1qipuA4vb2IggwBNTEM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been at this dentist for almost 3 years. They are very thorough with the cleanings and do more care than some other dentists, like keeping careful measure of the gum pockets. In particular, Shawn the hygienist has been so lovely. I got my first cavity filled recently, which was scary for me. She made sure I felt comfortable and kept me calm the whole time. They even topically numb your gums before you get the shot to fully numb your mouth. Following the filling, I needed a bite adjustment for the cavity filling. They were able to see me within 24 hours of calling. Shawn and Dr. Waind were just as kind, and got everything fixed in \u003c1 hour. I am thankful to have a dentist office that is so easy to schedule with and takes such good care of me!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rgkress","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvKEcmqzjsO2VLv2UywZ5GNnmIGaSZLv4oO5L_jN2yIz7EdA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best dentist around and I’ve known a few. My wife and I have been patients of Dr Nicolini for around 10 years and both of us are 100% satisfied. On my recommendation, my wife left her last dentist for Dr Nicloini (she works downtown), and she is now much happier than before.\n\nThe Dr is excellent, the staff friendly, skilled, and accommodating, and the office and equipment cutting edge modern. The office does its' own in-house work on crowns, so no need for multiple visits or long waits. If anything needs to be tweaked (crown-wise), it gets done on the spot!\n\nTooth cleaning, X-rays, and cavities have all been pain-free and professionally done the first time around. I am not a fan of going to the dentist, but I strongly recommend Rick Nicolini and his entire office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carmen Loh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3jORbJKizfA8CeRA3ZW12ivghNhGowMHddDOlsif2nwLHTEk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been a patient of this practice since 2008 and highly recommend it. Every hygienist I’ve worked with is knowledgeable, friendly, and they encouraged me to be better with my dental health without making me feel horrible. Dr. Waind is super pleasant as well. Extra points because they play fun music, not the boring stuff. Sometimes 80s alternative, sometimes 90s, was impressed to hear Selena this AM.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LJ C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJQxFxhjFmR4QTlBQLgAr4ws8y32w4f4r-xxGp6J5xbbL7bA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been a patient of Dr. Nicolini's for at least 15 years. I recall being referred to him by a co-worker who knew I hated going to the dentist.  I was pleasantly surprised at how friendly and knowledgeable they were.  I don't have to worry about having unnecessary dental work done. Dr. Nicolini has proven to be very trustworthy with conservative treatment.  I have referred him to several people.  I continue to be impressed with his and his entire staff's professionalism and quality of care.  They are mindful of patient comfort and pain-free care at all times.  Very convenient location downtown.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kristin Spaans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKHR6BchT9eOer5qJTTo3VyEzjeAJrEIoLE9-T5RLffBeHh8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this practice! Everyone who works here is super friendly. The staff will provide helpful tips on how to improve your oral health, and it always comes from a compassionate place instead of a judgmental one. The staff genuinely cares about their patients and what they do. I never wait more than a minute or two to get in for a scheduled appointment, so while the waiting room is nice, I never spend any time there. I’ll continue to visit for my dental needs as long as I live in Seattle!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angelina Fox","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaIgEcz9lG-Tznl4HYE_b2RzANkVVVgyW2UJ-r5vLyNbGE46mbDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hadn't gone to the dentist in a really long time, and finally mustered up the courage at the recommendation of a friend who had done the same. She wasn't wrong -- they are stellar here. They weren't at all condescending, were really patient and thoughtful, and they took the time to explain everything to me. I never felt rushed. The cleaning was also the fastest, most thorough, least painful cleaning I have ever had. SO great -- if I had more than two thumbs they would all be way up.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
